# CODEOWNERS — gates review requirements for sensitive paths.
#
# Purpose: Per /cso recommendation, any modification to CI/build infra, the
#   Homebrew tap formula, or supply-chain config (dependabot) must be reviewed
#   by the project owner. GitHub automatically requests review from listed
#   owners on any PR that touches a matched path.
# Process: GitHub reads this file from .github/CODEOWNERS on the base branch
#   of every PR. Last matching rule wins, so order from general to specific.
# Connections: Pairs with branch protection on `main` (configured in repo
#   settings, not in this file) which should enforce "Require review from
#   Code Owners" for merges. Matches .github/workflows/ci.yml,
#   Formula/lens.rb, .github/dependabot.yml.

# Default owner for everything in the repo.
*                       @cfelmer-ctrlhwo

# CI / supply-chain — explicit ownership so any pipeline change goes through
# the project owner even if a future broader rule relaxes the default.
/.github/               @cfelmer-ctrlhwo
/.github/workflows/     @cfelmer-ctrlhwo
/.github/CODEOWNERS     @cfelmer-ctrlhwo
/.github/dependabot.yml @cfelmer-ctrlhwo

# Homebrew tap formula — distribution artifact, must not change without review.
/Formula/               @cfelmer-ctrlhwo
